@page "/howuseimahe"

<PageTitle>How to Use Imahe</PageTitle>

<div class="how-to-use-wrapper">
    <div class="how-to-use-container">
        <div class="header-section">
            <span class="oi oi-book header-icon"></span>
            <div>
                <h1>How to Use Imahe</h1>
                <p class="lead">Follow these simple steps to get your photos sorted in minutes.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Important Notes Section -->
        <div class="alert alert-info d-flex align-items-center" role="alert">
            <span class="oi oi-lightbulb me-3" style="font-size: 1.5rem;"></span>
            <div>
                <h5 class="alert-heading">A Quick Heads-Up!</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li>For the best results, create two empty folders on your computer: one named <strong>INPUT</strong> and one named <strong>OUTPUT</strong>.</li>
                    <li>Please stay on the Sorting page while Imahe is processing your photos to ensure the process completes successfully.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Step-by-Step Guide -->
        <div class="steps-container">
            <div class="step-card">
                <div class="step-number">1</div>
                <div class="step-content">
                    <h3>Gather Your Photos</h3>
                    <p>
                        Copy all the photos you want to sort into your <strong>INPUT</strong> folder. Don't worry about duplicates or bad shots â€“ that's what Imahe is for!
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="step-card">
                <div class="step-number">2</div>
                <div class="step-content">
                    <h3>Set Your Preferences (Optional)</h3>
                    <p>
                        Navigate to the <strong>Settings</strong> page. Here, you can tell Imahe exactly how picky you want it to be about brightness and sharpness. The recommended defaults are a great starting point!
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="step-card">
                <div class="step-number">3</div>
                <div class="step-content">
                    <h3>Start Sorting</h3>
                    <p>
                        Go to the <strong>Sort</strong> page. Click the "Choose Input Folder" and "Choose Output Folder" buttons to select the folders you prepared in Step 1. Once selected, click the <strong>Start Processing</strong> button and let the AI work its magic!
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="step-card">
                <div class="step-number">4</div>
                <div class="step-content">
                    <h3>View Your Results</h3>
                    <p>
                        Once processing is complete, you can either click the <strong>View Results</strong> button to open your <strong>OUTPUT</strong> folder, or check the <strong>History</strong> page to see a detailed breakdown of the entire session. It's that simple!
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>


